Altech, Anglo, Calgro, Ellies, SOH: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-19T23:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/altech-anglo-calgro-ellies-soh-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 187.09, or 0.6
percent, to 32,058.68 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Allied Technologies Ltd. (ALT)  : The maker of television
set-top boxes holds its annual general meeting. Shares closed 61
cents, or 1 percent higher, at 60.79 rand.  Anglo American Plc (AAL)  : De Beers, in which Anglo owns
a 45 percent stake, is scheduled to resume wages talks with the
National Union of Mineworkers. Shares in Anglo rose 6.20 rand,
or 1.9 percent, to 332.20 rand.  Calgro M3 Holdings Ltd. (CGR)  : The housing developer
holds its annual general meeting. The stock closed unchanged at
70 cents.  Ellies Holdings Ltd. (ELI)  : The manufacturer of
satellite-television equipment, releases results for the year to
end April. Shares fell 3 cents, or 1.4 percent, to 2.05 rand.  South Ocean Holdings Ltd. (SOH)  : The maker of power
cables said headline earnings per share and earnings per share
for the six months to June 30 were expected to be 25 percent to
35 percent lower than the corresponding prior period. The stock
fell 3 cents, or 1.8 percent, to 1.65 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
